voice recorder on macbook is there a voice recorder on macbook if so where is it yes it depends on what version of macbook you have if you have a newer mac there should be a program called garageband you can use this to record music or in this case voice it comes installed and is on your dock bottom of your scree by default the icon is a guitar open up garage band click new music project click create dont worry about that other stuff just click create on the top toolbar click track then new track and on the screen that comes up click real instrument then when you are ready to record click the round button with the red circle in the middle on the bottom of the window to begin recording hope this helps Taskbar Mouse (computing) Windows XP IPod AmigaOS Macromedia Flash Macintosh Finder ILife Minesweeper (computer game) Icon (computing) Screenshot Object Desktop Mac OS X Double-click (computing) History of the graphical user interface 2Step Tungsten Handheld Opera (web browser) Apple Macintosh Emacs Dance Dance Revolution International Phonetic Alphabet ITunes Spyware Microsoft Windows Pop-up ad X Window System Stardock AppleScript Palm OS GarageBand Microsoft Paint Apple Computer Hello world program The Sims 2: University Disc jockey Finale notation program Comparison of file systems Windows Mobile QuickTime Space Quest Twm Visual Basic System 6 Expos__ (Mac OS X) Visual Basic .NET Inkscape Linspire Window Maker Windows Picture and Fax Viewer The Wildhearts Mac OS X v10.4 Dock (computing) Qt (toolkit) OmniWeb Start Menu Windows 3.x Girls Aloud Halo: Combat Evolved Dance Dance Revolution EXTREME Multiple document interface New Order Google Desktop Synthesizer Internet Explorer OpenOffice.org Blood on the Tracks Warcraft II MSN Messenger Flight Unlimited II Context menu Microsoft Office Gothic metal The Chemical Brothers Apple II family Homestar Runner Silverchair System 7 (Macintosh) Mahjong Sega Mega Drive/Sega Genesis Microsoft Word Sampling (music) Unicode Comparison